name: addSegment
description: Add new segment to scope.

params.name: id
params.description: If of this segment.

params.name: start
params.description: Index of first character of this segment.

params.name: end
params.description: Index of first character after this segment.

params.name: options
params.description: Optional parameters.

params.name: options.uses
params.description:
Array of other segments which should be
considered as part of this segment.

params.name: options.usesPointers
params.description:
Array of pointers needed for
this segment. Basically this means variables which this segment is using.

params.name: options.pointer
params.description:
If this segment is going to create a
new variable this would be the pointer to it.

params.name: options.label
params.description:
If this segment is going to create a new
label this would be the pointer to it.

params.name: options.exposes
params.description:
If this segment is going to expose
something outside of scope.

name: src/utils/validate/isNumber.js
isNumber
description: Check if value is number.
examples:
isNumber(10);        // true
isNumber(438.34);    // true
isNumber(NaN);       // false
isNumber({});        // false
isNumber('124');     // false
isNumber(Infinity);  // false

params.name: value
params.description: Value to test.

name: src/utils/validate/isUndefined.js
isUndefined
description: Check if value is undefined.
examples:
isUndefined();             // true
isUndefined(undefined);    // true
isUndefined('undefined');  // false
isUndefined(null);         // false

params.name: value
params.description: Value to test.

name: src/utils/validate/isWithinRange.js
isWithinRange
description: Check if values (start and end) are within range of another.
examples:
isWithinRange(10, 20, 5, 30);  // true
isWithinRange(2, 20, 5, 30);   // false
isWithinRange(15, 35, 5, 30);  // false

params.name: xStart
params.description: Start value you want to be within another range.

params.name: xEnd
params.description: End value you want to be within another range.

params.name: yStart
params.description: Start value of what you test against.

params.name: yEnd
params.description: End value of what you test against.

content:
# Regression Analysis
[work in process]

[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/vanils/regana.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/vanils/regana)
[![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/vanils/regana/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/vanils/regana)
[![Dependency Status](https://david-dm.org/vanils/regana.svg)](https://david-dm.org/vanils/regana)
[![devDependency Status](https://david-dm.org/vanils/regana/dev-status.svg)](https://david-dm.org/vanils/regana#info=devDependencies)

Tool to analyse risk for regressions. Can be integrated with Github pull requests to highlight potential issues and used by QA people to plan regression tests.

Read more from [API documentation](https://vanils.github.io/regana/)

{
  "bin": {
    "regana": "./bin/regana.js"
  },
  "engines": {
    "node": ">=8"
  },
  "name": "regana",
  "version": "1.1.15",
  "description": "Tool to analyse risk for regressions based on git diff",
  "main": "src/regana.js",
  "scripts": {
    "docs": "node ./node_modules/.bin/rmdir-cli docs && ./node_modules/.bin/esdoc -c .esdoc.json",
    "build": "node console.log('build');",
    "start": "node console.log('start');",
    "test": "node ./node_modules/.bin/jest --config=.jestrc.json",
    "lint": "node ./node_modules/.bin/eslint --ignore-pattern=**/mocks/** --config=.eslintrc.json src/**/** bin/**/**",
    "codecov": "node ./node_modules/.bin/codecov",
    "commitmsg": "commitlint -e $GIT_PARAMS",
    "precommit": "npm run test && npm run lint"
  },
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "https://github.com/vanils/regana.git"
  },
  "keywords": [
    "regression"
  ],
  "author": "Matti Mehtonen",
  "license": "MIT",
  "bugs": {
    "url": "https://github.com/vanils/regana/issues"
  },
  "homepage": "https://github.com/vanils/regana#readme",
  "dependencies": {
    "babylon": "^6.18.0",
    "minimist": "^1.2.0",
    "uniqid": "^4.1.1"
  },
  "devDependencies": {

    "chalk": "^2.4.1",
    "codecov": "^3.0.2",
    "esdoc": "^1.1.0",
    "esdoc-standard-plugin": "^1.0.0",
    "eslint": "^4.19.1",
    "eslint-plugin-jest": "^21.15.1",
    "eslint-plugin-jsdoc": "^3.6.3",
    "husky": "^0.14.3",
    "jest": "^22.4.3",
    "jsdoc": "^3.5.5",
    "please-upgrade-node": "^3.0.2",
    "rmdir-cli": "^2.0.6",
    "semantic-release": "^15.4.0",
    "taffydb": "^2.7.3"
  }
}
